00041 typedef struct KeyBlock {
00042     struct KeyBlock *next, *prev;
00043 
00044     float pos;         /* point in time   (Key->type == KEY_NORMAL) only,
00045                         * for historic reasons this is relative to (Key->ctime / 100),
00046                         * so this value increments by 0.1f per frame. */
00047     float curval;      /* influence (typically [0 - 1] but can be more), (Key->type == KEY_RELATIVE) only.*/
00048 
00049     short type;        /* interpolation type (Key->type == KEY_NORMAL) only. */
00050     short pad1;
00051 
00052     short relative;    /* relative == 0 means first key is reference, otherwise the index of Key->blocks */
00053     short flag;
00054 
00055     int totelem;       /* total number if items in the keyblock (compare with mesh/curve verts to check we match) */
00056     int uid;           /* for meshes only, match the unique number with the customdata layer */
00057     
00058     void  *data;       /* array of shape key values, size is (Key->elemsize * KeyBlock->totelem) */
00059     float *weights;    /* store an aligned array of weights from 'vgroup' */
00060     char   name[64];   /* MAX_NAME (unique name, user assigned) */
00061     char   vgroup[64]; /* MAX_VGROUP_NAME (optional vertex group), array gets allocated into 'weights' when set */
00062 
00063     /* ranges, for RNA and UI only to clamp 'curval' */
00064     float slidermin;
00065     float slidermax;
00066 
00067 } KeyBlock;

00070 typedef struct Key {
00071     ID id;
00072     struct AnimData *adt;   /* animation data (must be immediately after id for utilities to use it) */ 
00073 
00074     /* commonly called 'Basis', (Key->type == KEY_RELATIVE) only.
00075      * Looks like this is  _always_ 'key->block.first',
00076      * perhaps later on it could be defined as some other KeyBlock - campbell */
00077     KeyBlock *refkey;
00078 
00079     /* this is not a regular string, although it is \0 terminated
00080      * this is an array of (element_array_size, element_type) pairs
00081      * (each one char) used for calculating shape key-blocks */
00082     char elemstr[32];
00083     int elemsize;  /* size of each element in #KeyBlock.data, use for allocation and stride */
00084     int pad;
00085     
00086     ListBase block;  /* list of KeyBlock's */
00087     struct Ipo *ipo  DNA_DEPRECATED;  /* old animation system, deprecated for 2.5 */
00088 
00089     ID *from;
00090 
00091     short type;    /* absolute or relative shape key */
00092     short totkey;  /* (totkey == BLI_countlist(&key->block)) */
00093     short slurph;  /* quaint feature to delay moving points based on their order (Key->type == KEY_NORMAL) only */
00094     short flag;
00095 
00096     /* only used when (Key->type == KEY_NORMAL), this value is used as a time slider,
00097      * rather then using the scenes time, this value can be animated to give greater control */
00098     float ctime;
00099 
00100     /* can never be 0, this is used for detecting old data */
00101     int uidgen; /* current free uid for keyblocks */
00102 } Key;
